---
const narrative = [
  { era: 'Science', desc: 'Neuroscience researcher, two peer-reviewed publications' },
  { era: 'Media', desc: 'Video producer and online education platform builder' },
  { era: 'Product', desc: 'Agency PM, then first PM hire at a B2B marketplace' },
  { era: 'Operations', desc: 'VP of Customer Success, then VP of Strategic Ops' },
  { era: 'Builder', desc: 'Leading teams and orchestrating generative engineering workflows' },
];

const metrics = [
  { value: '7', suffix: '+', label: 'teams & orgs built from zero' },
  { value: '10', suffix: '+', label: 'industries crossed' },
  { value: '14', suffix: 'yrs', label: 'in product & operations' },
  { value: '2', suffix: '', label: 'peer-reviewed publications' },
];
---
<section class="container py-24">
  <div class="reveal">
    <h2 class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-widest text-accent mb-12">The Arc</h2>
  </div>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-start">
    <!-- Left: Bio -->
    <div>
      <div class="reveal">
        <p class="text-lg text-fg leading-relaxed mb-6">
          I started in a neuroscience lab, then moved into video production where I ran the
          full process: finding ideas, market research, working with professors, writing scripts,
          directing, post-production, and releasing into a managed YouTube channel. That led me
          to build an online education platform from scratch for 1,000+ students.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="reveal" style="transition-delay: 0.08s">
        <p class="text-fg-muted leading-relaxed mb-6">
          From there I went deep into technology at a Brooklyn agency, working with entrepreneurs
          and institutions as a PM to validate ideas, define strategy, and lead agile sprints with
          designers and developers. One of those clients hired me as their first PM. Over seven
          years I built their product and design team, stood up Customer Success with the full
          playbook of onboarding, retention, QBRs, and upselling, then redesigned their entire
          sales operation: BANT process, outbound campaigns, cold call scripts, pipeline tracking,
          and enablement infrastructure.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="reveal" style="transition-delay: 0.16s">
        <p class="text-fg-muted leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Now I'm in industrial safety, working with a small team of engineers, data scientists,
          and ML consultants to build an AI-powered camera system. I handle everything from lead
          generation and pilot conversion to compliance documentation, the marketing site, and
          the safety analytics dashboard. We're training the AI to classify incidents through
          manual annotation and teaching it to surface the must-see items on its own, so it
          becomes a true safety agent for the factory floor.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="reveal" style="transition-delay: 0.24s">
        <p class="text-fg-muted leading-relaxed">
          Across all of it, the constant is how I work: heavy on planning and review, building
          self-evolving processes, optimizing teams into tight loops of strategy, execution, and
          retrospectives. I read a lot, think in systems, and focus on proving hypotheses before
          scaling them. Two peer-reviewed publications in neuroscience gave me that discipline,
          and it never left.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Right: Narrative Arc -->
    <div class="space-y-0">
      {narrative.map((item, i) => (
        <div class="reveal flex items-start gap-4 py-4 border-b border-border last:border-0" style={`transition-delay: ${i * 0.08}s`}>
          <span class="text-accent font-mono text-sm font-medium min-w-[90px]">{item.era}</span>
          <span class="text-fg-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">{item.desc}</span>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Metrics bar -->
  <div class="grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-4 gap-8 mt-20 pt-10 border-t border-border">
    {metrics.map((m, i) => (
      <div class="reveal text-center sm:text-left" style={`transition-delay: ${i * 0.1}s`}>
        <div class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-white metric-value leading-none">
          {m.value}<span class="text-accent">{m.suffix}</span>
        </div>
        <div class="text-xs text-fg-muted mt-2 font-mono leading-snug">{m.label}</div>
      </div>
    ))}
  </div>
</section>
